page.title: 10THE MEADOWS
page.content: We went for a walk in the {fields}to see what {plants}there were. The field was large with untrimmed hedges and trees. There were a lot of dead trees. We thought that they had been killed off by {Dutch Elm Disease.}It was quite damp at the lower end of the field with a small stream running beside the hedge. Part of the field was used by{cattle}and part was fenced off for{hay.}A massive raised water pipe runs through the lower half of the field. Under this it is overgrown with newly seeded weeds because the ground was chewed up by some machinery used for mending the pipe last year.
